# Research-Grade Semiconductor Manufacturing Intelligence Framework

## Project Overview

This project presents a research-grade semiconductor wafer anomaly detection and manufacturing intelligence framework designed for advanced quality assurance and process monitoring. The framework integrates statistical methods, machine learning algorithms, dimensionality reduction techniques, and ensemble intelligence to identify abnormal manufacturing behavior, rank operational risks, and support proactive defect prevention.

Unlike traditional threshold-based monitoring systems, this solution leverages multivariate anomaly detection and latent feature extraction to uncover hidden process deviations within semiconductor fabrication environments.

---

# Research Objectives

The primary objectives of this study are:

- Detect anomalous wafer manufacturing conditions.
- Identify hidden process abnormalities.
- Reduce dimensionality while preserving critical information.
- Analyze latent manufacturing factors using Principal Component Analysis.
- Compare multiple anomaly detection techniques.
- Develop a robust ensemble risk scoring system.
- Provide actionable manufacturing intelligence through visual analytics.

